  "longBusinessSummary": "M. Dias Branco S.A. Ind\u00fastria e Com\u00e9rcio de Alimentos manufactures, distributes, and sells food products in Brazil. It offers cookies and crackers, pasta, and wheat flour/bran; vegetable shortenings and margarines, cakes, cake mixes, packaged toast, and snacks; and cereals, snacks, granolas, gluten-free products, seasonings, sauces, and condiments under the Adria, Aldente, Basilar, Bonsabor, Estrela, Fortaleza, Finna, Fit Food, Frontera, Isabela, Jasmine, Pel\u00e1gio, Pilar, Piraqu\u00ea, Predilleto, Richester, Salsito, Smart, Taste&Co, Treloso, Vitarella, Zabet, and Las Acacias brands. The company also provides refined oils and wheat milling services. In addition, it exports its products. The company was founded in 1936 and is headquartered in Eus\u00e9bio, Brazil.",
